    "description": "Bayesian modelling of DNA methylation heterogeneity at single-cell resolution.\n\nHere we introduce scMET, a Bayesian framework for the analysis of single cell DNA methylation data. This modelling approach combines a hierarchical beta-binomial specification with a generalised linear model framework with the aim of capturing biological overdispersion and overcome data sparsity by sharing information across cells and genomic features.",
